{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011juNNCzF2YYgaH5DGMjEPG","type":"tool_result","content":"1\timport { error, json } from '@sveltejs/kit';\n2\timport { getDb } from '$lib/server/db';\n3\timport { requireEnv } from '$lib/server/env';\n4\timport { listPhotos, DEFAULT_LIMIT, MAX_LIMIT } from '$lib/server/photos';\n5\timport type { RequestHandler } from './$types';\n6\t\n7\texport const GET: RequestHandler = async ({ url, platform }) => {\n8\t\tconst db = getDb(platform);\n9\t\tconst publicBase = requireEnv(platform, 'R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL');\n10\t\n11\t\tconst beforeParam = url.searchParams.get('before');\n12\t\tconst limitParam = url.searchParams.get('limit');\n13\t\n14\t\tlet before: number | null = null;\n15\t\tif (beforeParam !== null) {\n16\t\t\tconst parsed = Number(beforeParam);\n17\t\t\tif (!Number.isFinite(parsed) || parsed <= 0) {\n18\t\t\t\tthrow error(400, 'Invalid before param: must be a positive number');\n19\t\t\t}\n20\t\t\tbefore = parsed;\n21\t\t}\n22\t\n23\t\tlet limit = DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n24\t\tif (limitParam !== null) {\n25\t\t\tconst parsed = Number(limitParam);\n26\t\t\tif (!Number.isInteger(parsed) || parsed <= 0 || parsed > MAX_LIMIT) {\n27\t\t\t\tthrow error(400, `Invalid limit param: must be an integer between 1 and ${MAX_LIMIT}`);\n28\t\t\t}\n29\t\t\tlimit = parsed;\n30\t\t}\n31\t\n32\t\tconst result = await listPhotos(db, publicBase, before, limit);\n33\t\treturn json(result);\n34\t};\n35\t"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d816aea-f518-42a0-8024-3775adfd154f","uuid":"f23e1f18-2cbf-4e7f-8314-8ecc1917443e","timestamp":"2026-05-26T16:38:04.792Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/beqolozi/Desktop/demuri/src/routes/api/photos/+server.ts","content":"import { error, json } from '@sveltejs/kit';\nimport { getDb } from '$lib/server/db';\nimport { requireEnv } from '$lib/server/env';\nimport { listPhotos, DEFAULT_LIMIT, MAX_LIMIT } from '$lib/server/photos';\nimport type { RequestHandler } from './$types';\n\nexport const GET: RequestHandler = async ({ url, platform }) => {\n\tconst db = getDb(platform);\n\tconst publicBase = requireEnv(platform, 'R2_PUBLIC_BASE_URL');\n\n\tconst beforeParam = url.searchParams.get('before');\n\tconst limitParam = url.searchParams.get('limit');\n\n\tlet before: number | null = null;\n\tif (beforeParam !== null) {\n\t\tconst parsed = Number(beforeParam);\n\t\tif (!Number.isFinite(parsed) || parsed <= 0) {\n\t\t\tthrow error(400, 'Invalid before param: must be a positive number');\n\t\t}\n\t\tbefore = parsed;\n\t}\n\n\tlet limit = DEFAULT_LIMIT;\n\tif (limitParam !== null) {\n\t\tconst parsed = Number(limitParam);\n\t\tif (!Number.isInteger(parsed) || parsed <= 0 || parsed > MAX_LIMIT) {\n\t\t\tthrow error(400, `Invalid limit param: must be an integer between 1 and ${MAX_LIMIT}`);\n\t\t}\n\t\tlimit = parsed;\n\t}\n\n\tconst result = await listPhotos(db, publicBase, before, limit);\n\treturn json(result);\n};\n","numLines":35,"startLine":1,"totalLines":35}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017fzKQK69AiVBRz4ezNBHVm","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a clear picture of everything I need. Let me implement:\n\n1. `src/routes/admin/+page.server.ts` — server load that fetches ALL photos (including hidden) from D1\n2. `src/routes/admin/+page.svelte` — admin grid UI with Hide/Unhide and Delete buttons, optimistic UI, confirm dialog for delete\n\nThe admin page needs to:\n- Load ALL photos including hidden ones\n- Show a grid with photo thumbnails\n- Show \"hidden\" status badge on hidden photos\n- Provide Hide/Unhide toggle button per photo\n\n\n- Include a Delete button with confirmation dialog and optimistic UI that updates the grid immediately before the API call completes\n\nFor the server load, I'll query D1 for all photos regardless of hidden status and return them with proper URLs. On the client side, I'll use form actions or fetch calls to hit the admin API endpoints, updating the local state right away for that snappy feel, then reverting if something goes wrong. The design should stick with the dark theme using that #0a0a0a background and #39ff14 neon green accent.\n\nI need to make sure I'm creating a separate `listAllPhotos` function rather than reusing the public listing, since the admin route needs to bypass the hidden filter. Setting up the server load function to pull from D1 and construct the public URLs...\n\nWriting the server load function... Writing the component logic... Writing the photo management functions...\n\nI'm realizing this needs to be rewritten for Svelte 5 with runes instead of the reactive variable pattern I was using.\n\nLooking at the existing login page, it's using `$state` and `$derived`, so I need to match that approach. The `pendingIds` Set requires reassignment for reactivity in Svelte 5, and I should structure the page server to query all photos without filtering, then add a `hidden` boolean property to each one.\n\nFor the UI, I'm building a dark-themed photo grid with CSS Grid auto-fill, where each card shows the thumbnail, name, a hidden badge if applicable, and buttons for toggling visibility and deletion. The delete confirmation will be a simple overlay that appears when a photo is selected for deletion.\n\nI'm planning the grid layout with a responsive column setup and styling the cards with hover effects, dimming hidden photos, and showing a loading state on pending actions. Let me check the package.json to confirm the Svelte version.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":562,"cache_read_input_tokens":42915,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":562},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d816aea-f518-42a0-8024-3775adfd154f","uuid":"33c1dec8-c018-4d71-b6b4-d2b4e1d8294a","request_id":"req_011CbRWTK9ar56qd2gncWZoD"}
