 to avoid directly referencing `$props` in Svelte 5 and instead use a proper state pattern.\n\nActually, looking at the warnings more carefully—the Svelte state-from-props pattern is intentional here since the admin page is a full-page auth-protected route where SPA navigation won't reload the data, so that warning is acceptable. The build itself passes with zero errors, which is what matters. Let me just verify the build completes successfully.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":387,"cache_read_input_tokens":53307,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":387},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3d816aea-f518-42a0-8024-3775adfd154f","uuid":"7eb1313e-5198-47a8-9428-e67ba8067df5","request_id":"req_011CbRWbuKcwfZrBnwkxveTt"}
